      %h3 Never lose a thing.
      %p Connect DigitalPost to cloud storage, such as Amazon Web Service's S3, and never worry about the delete key, power surges, or errant PCVs.
  %hr
  .row
    .span12
      %h2 Find what you need, when you need it.
      %p.lead DigitalPost is designed to run with an ElasticSearch server, providing you finely-tuned search results.
      %p Stop wading through pages of documents, or returning hundreds of meaningless responses to your searches. Staff and Volunteers will be happier and more productive, having the tools they need at the tips of their fingers.
  %hr
  .row
    .span12
      %h2 Add another DigitalPost. Connect it to the rest.
      %p.lead Rinse, lather, repeat.
      %p By using a shared ElasticSearch index, allow each of your DigitalPost instances to search the rest. Stop re-inventing the wheel, and share your innovations.
  %hr
  .row
    .span12
      %h2 Build your own features.
      %p.lead Want a new feature? Hate something already there?
      %p With a code base as open as a store on black Friday, and as free as a beer at a family barbecue, feel free to hack away. Because we've built DigitalPost using the Ruby on Rails framework, and adhered to open standards, your in-house developers will find it easy to modify.
